A female Marine who was killed in a helicopter crash on Friday was a highly decorated Afghanistan veteran.

Captain Elizabeth Kealey, 32, had been in the Marine Corps for almost 10 years and was deployed twice with the 13th Marine Expeditionary Unit serving one tour in Afghanistan. 

She was serving as a helicopter pilot and weapons training instructor when her aircraft went down at the Marine Corps Air Ground Combat Center in Twentynine Palms on Friday afternoon.  

