Captain Kealey, from Indiana, Pennsylvania had earned several awards and medals including the Air Medal with three Strike/Flight awards and the Navy and Marine Corps Achievement Medal with gold star in lieu of second award. 

She died alongside fellow Marine First Lieutenant Adam Satterfield who was working alongside her when their helicopter crashed during a military training exercise.

They both died as a result of crash injuries. No one else was on board  the UH-1Y Huey helicopter at the time.

